If there are also open review feedback issues (description references a commit SHA), address those with fixup commits: git commit --fixup=<sha>

After creating a fixup commit, check whether your changes affect code that later commits also touch:
1. Run git log --oneline <target-sha>..HEAD to list downstream commits.
2. If your fixup renamed an identifier, changed a function signature, modified an interface, or altered a type that later commits reference, create additional fixup commits for each affected downstream commit.
3. Each additional fixup must target the correct downstream SHA: git commit --fixup=<downstream-sha>

Rules:
- One commit per issue.
- Run tests before committing.
- Do not create new beads issues.
